description.text:
My wife was horrified when our 9-year-old son slammed the bathroom door shut and noticed that the huge mirror on the back of the door almost fell off. Three of the six mirror holders were broken. I then checked the other doors, and two other bathrooms had three holders missing each! What a disaster that could have been.  
My son said &quot;Why not just print some?&quot;  
I said &quot;Oh, great idea, I am glad that I thought of it. I will make some.&quot;  
My wife said that I should run to Lowe's in the morning and buy more holders. I replied &quot;Why buy something for $1.96 per pack when I can spend hours designing and making my own?&quot;  
In reality it only took a few minutes to model. At first I was going to copy the existing ones exactly, but then I realized that they were not all that good looking - so I designed them how I thought best - and will just replace them all.  
These are for 1/4&quot; thick glass.
